# Supabase Patterns

## RLS Policy Required

Every new table MUST have an RLS policy. Without it, the anon key returns zero rows:

```sql
ALTER TABLE my_table ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Allow all my_table" ON my_table FOR ALL TO anon, authenticated USING (true) WITH CHECK (true);
```

## Agent Filtering (Date-Aware)

Never use `.eq("is_active", true)` alone. Always account for `terminated_date`:

```typescript
const filtered = agents.filter((a) => {
  if (a.is_active) return true;
  if (a.terminated_date && targetDate < a.terminated_date) return true;
  return false;
});
```

## Map/Set Iteration

TypeScript target requires `Array.from()` wrapper for Map/Set iteration:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
for (const [key, val] of Array.from(myMap)) { ... }
for (const item of Array.from(mySet)) { ... }

// ❌ Will cause TS2802 error
for (const [key, val] of myMap) { ... }
```

## Edge Functions

Edge functions use Deno. Import from `@supabase/supabase-js` via URL imports. Environment variables via `Deno.env.get()`.
